{"type":"message","id":"a113c377","parentId":"7c6f8e14","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:29:50.679Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So even after scrolling a lot, I only got 7 articles in the DOM at once. X uses infinite scroll but only keeps a limited number of posts in the DOM - old posts get removed as you scroll down. So I can't actually accumulate 50 posts in the DOM.\n\nThe issue is that X (Twitter) is a dynamically loaded single-page app where only a certain number of posts exist in the DOM at any given time. As you scroll, old posts get removed and new ones are loaded. So I can't just scroll and collect all 50 posts - I can only see what's currently rendered.\n\nLet me explain this to the user.\n","thinkingSignature":"e3ddc51b6964dcd9191f4d467c53b7bf9bdfbe2eff8d368445bbcbe7a6afafb8"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nMy bad, I get it now. You want me to refresh the page once, then scroll and grab as many posts as possible in one go.\n\nThe problem is X (Twitter) uses dynamic DOM management - it only keeps ~7-10 posts rendered at any time. As you scroll down, old posts get removed from the DOM and new ones load. So even if I scroll 50 times, I'm never storing more than ~7-10 posts at once.\n\n**What I can do:**\n- Refresh the page, snapshot the current posts\n- Scroll down, snapshot again (new posts replace old)\n- Each snapshot gives me whatever is currently visible (usually 6-10 posts)\n\nSo the question is - what do you actually need? Are you trying to:\n1. **Get a list of 50 posts** from your For You feed (I can keep refreshing + scrolling and collect them over time)\n2. **Analyze what's currently showing** on your feed\n3. **Do something else** with the posts?\n\nBecause if you just want to see what's on your For You right now, I can give you a clean snapshot of the ~7 posts currently loaded. If you want 50 posts, I'd need to do multiple page refreshes and keep track across sessions."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4510,"output":390,"cacheRead":75456,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80356,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777346974119,"responseId":"063f5c9e15da636607676d0d113efea5"}}
