{"type":"compaction","id":"f01a3b91","parentId":"d79f6069","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:33:53.380Z","summary":"\n\n## Goal\nScrape ~50 posts from the user's X (Twitter) For You feed by refreshing the page once and then scrolling through to capture content.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Refresh the page only ONCE (not multiple refreshes)\n- Scroll continuously to grab as many posts as possible in one pass\n- User clarified they wanted one page load + one continuous scroll, not repeated refresh + snapshot cycles\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Confirmed browser is enabled and working (Chrome, CDP, running)\n- [x] Verified X is logged into @BobbyGalletta account\n- [x] Identified that X's DOM only keeps ~6-10 posts rendered at any time regardless of scroll depth\n- [x] Discovered X removes old posts from DOM as new ones load (infinite scroll with lazy unloading)\n- [x] Collected ~50 posts across multiple scroll + snapshot cycles in initial attempt (before user clarified intent)\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Awaiting clarification from user on what they actually want to do with the posts (list analysis, current snapshot, or alternative approach)\n\n### Blocked\n- Technical limitation: X's DOM management prevents accumulating 50+ posts in a single session — only ~7-10 posts exist in DOM at any scroll position\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Using browser evaluate with setTimeout scrolls instead of fast loops**: Attempted slower scrolling with delays to let content load; still resulted in only 7-8 articles in DOM\n- **Explained DOM limitation to user**: Posted that X dynamically unloads posts as you scroll, so 50 posts cannot be captured in one continuous pass\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Wait for user to clarify goal: (a) get list of 50 posts over multiple sessions, (b) analyze current feed, or (c) alternative task\n2. If they want a list of 50, plan multiple page loads with persistent tracking\n3. If they want current feed analysis, provide clean snapshot of currently visible ~7 posts\n\n## Critical Context\n- Browser targetId: `097BA166492C4CA2D14542621CE7B0D3`\n- X URL: `https://x.com/home`\n- Account: @BobbyGalletta\n- Posts from initial collection (~50) included: Julian Goldie SEO (OpenClaw content), Elon Musk (WW11 post), Vadim (Claude Code proxy), GTA San Andreas trailer, Miami XO bazooka video, and various AI/tech/political/viral content\n- When counting articles via JS: `document.querySelectorAll('article').length` — returns ~5-8 max regardless of scroll depth\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n\n\n## Original Request\nThe user asked the assistant to take note of posts visible before scrolling, then scroll through X's \"For You\" feed to collect a list of 50 posts total.\n\n## Early Progress\nThe assistant navigated to x.com/home, took snapshots, and started saving posts to a markdown file at `/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x/x_for_you_posts.md`. Nine posts have been collected so far:\n\n1. @JulianGoldieSEO - local AI agent build guide\n2. @eclincher - AI Social Media Agent ad\n3. @boxmining - OpenClaw 4.24 release\n4. @DHSgov - \"ICE is NICE\" repost\n5. @AntoineRSX - Chinese AI that builds games from prompts\n6. @googlegemma - local Gemma 4 browser agent\n7. @elonmusk - OpenAI \"charity theft\" accusations\n8. @plutusmedia - UGC agency ad\n9. @gregisenberg - OpenAI Codex masterclass\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe assistant is continuing to scroll in batches of 600px, taking snapshots, and adding each newly discovered post to the markdown file. The last snapshot was taken but its full contents were truncated. The assistant needs to continue this scroll-snapshot-save cycle approximately 40+ more times to reach 50 posts total.\n\n<read-files>\n/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/browser/skills/browser-automation/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x/x_for_you_posts.md\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"cd81d2e8","tokensBefore":133576,"details":{"readFiles":["/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/browser/skills/browser-automation/SKILL.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x/x_for_you_posts.md"]},"fromHook":false}
