{"type":"compaction","id":"d545ab93","parentId":"a03d27e2","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:39:58.381Z","summary":"\n\n## Goal\nScrape ~50 posts from the user's X (Twitter) For You feed by refreshing the page once and then scrolling through to capture content.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Refresh the page only ONCE (not multiple refreshes)\n- Scroll continuously to grab as many posts as possible in one pass\n- User clarified they wanted one page load + one continuous scroll, not repeated refresh + snapshot cycles\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Confirmed browser is enabled and working (Chrome, CDP, running)\n- [x] Verified X is logged into @BobbyGalletta account\n- [x] Identified that X's DOM only keeps ~6-10 posts rendered at any time regardless of scroll depth\n- [x] Discovered X removes old posts from DOM as new ones load (infinite scroll with lazy unloading)\n- [x] Collected 12 posts so far in current session:\n  1. @JulianGoldieSEO - local AI agent build guide\n  2. @eclincher - AI Social Media Agent ad\n  3. @boxmining - OpenClaw 4.24 release\n  4. @DHSgov - \"ICE is NICE\" repost\n  5. @AntoineRSX - Chinese AI that builds games from prompts\n  6. @googlegemma - local Gemma 4 browser agent\n  7. @elonmusk - OpenAI \"charity theft\" accusations\n  8. @plutusmedia - UGC agency ad\n  9. @gregisenberg - OpenAI Codex masterclass\n  10. @sairahul1 - VibeVoice ASR (830K views, 3K likes, 4.8K bookmarks)\n  11. @NousResearch - Hermes agent running TouchDesigner (44K views, 876 likes)\n  12. @maverickecom - Claude + Arcads for 550 slideshow posts/day (17K views, 170 likes)\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Continuing to scroll and snapshot to gather remaining posts toward goal of 50\n- [ ] Working around X's overlapping/duplicate content issue\n\n### Blocked\n- Technical limitation: X's DOM dynamically unloads posts as you scroll — only ~7-10 posts exist in DOM at any scroll position, making it impossible to accumulate 50 unique posts in one continuous session\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Using browser evaluate with setTimeout scrolls instead of fast loops**: Attempted slower scrolling with delays to let content load; still resulted in only 7-8 articles in DOM\n- **Continuing to try despite DOM limitation**: Assistant keeps scrolling and snapshotting, hoping to capture more unique posts as feed refreshes\n- **Using larger scroll increments (600-800px)**: Attempting to skip past duplicate content more quickly\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Continue scrolling and snapshotting in batches to capture as many posts as possible before feed stabilizes\n2. If still unable to reach 50, document exact limitation and suggest alternative approaches (multiple page loads, selective analysis, or programmatic collection)\n3. Monitor if feed eventually provides fresh content vs. continuing to repeat same posts\n\n## Critical Context\n- Browser targetId: `097BA166492C4CA2D14542621CE7B0D3`\n- X URL: `https://x.com/home`\n- Account: @BobbyGalletta\n- Output file: `/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x/x_for_you_posts.md`\n- When counting articles via JS: `document.querySelectorAll('article').length` — returns ~5-8 max regardless of scroll depth\n- Feed appears to be repeating same posts after initial scroll cycles — likely X caching same content per session\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Summary\n\n**User Request:** Collect 50 posts from X's \"For You\" feed by noting posts visible before scrolling, then scrolling repeatedly to accumulate posts.\n\n**Progress Made:** Assistant developed a scroll-snapshot-save strategy to work around X's DOM limitation (~6-10 posts in memory at once). Started with 12 posts from initial read, then through multiple scroll cycles captured posts 13-27. Posts include content about AI agents, tech news, viral videos, ads, and trending topics. The feed began cycling through the same ~26-27 posts repeatedly.\n\n**Suffix Context:** Assistant just performed another scroll (800px) and snapshot. Analyzing the new snapshot to identify any new posts beyond the ~27 already captured. Feed has been cycling with diminishing returns on new content.\n\n<read-files>\n/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/browser/skills/browser-automation/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x/x_for_you_posts.md\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"89b3f975","tokensBefore":137351,"details":{"readFiles":["/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/browser/skills/browser-automation/SKILL.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x/x_for_you_posts.md"]},"fromHook":false}
